The most closesly related species is: Dobsonia_viridis, Epomophorus wahlbergi, Syconycteris austrais, Cynopterus sphinx 
This phylogeny shows how ACE2 genes are related in different bat species. Since ACE2 is the receptor used by SARS-like viruses, 
comparing these sequences helps identify which bats may be more likely to interact with similar viruses
